OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FWorrying numbers of older  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fchildren having energy     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fdrinks regularly           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Up to a third of UK children - mostly  
OL,6, young teens - consume at least one     
OL,7, energy drink a week, while some are    
OL,8, having them almost daily, new research 
OL,9, suggests.                              
OL,11,FThose who drink lots may get headaches 
OL,12,Fand sleep problems, warn the authors of
OL,13,Fa report in the BMJ Open.              
OL,15,FHigh consumption is also linked to     
OL,16,Fworse educational outcomes.            
OL,18,FMany shops already stop under-16s from 
OL,19,Fbuying the drinks, which can be high in
OL,20,Fcaffeine, sugar and other stimulants.  
